The paper discusses the use of data-intensive and compute-intensive ecosystems, which are common topics in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on machine learning approaches, which are covered in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of ptychographic image reconstruction pipelines and distributed deep learning applications suggests that the paper may also fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the integration of Big Data processing platforms and HPC technologies, which could be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
